===Etymology===
From {{etyl|enm}} {{term|beginnen|lang=enm}}, from {{etyl|ang|en}} {{term|beginnan||to begin|lang=ang}}, from {{etyl|gem-pro|en}} {{recons|biginnanan||to begin|lang=gem-pro}} (compare West Frisian {{term|begjinne|lang=fy}}, {{etyl|nl|-}}/{{etyl|de|-}} {{term|beginnen}}), from {{etyl|ine-pro|en}} {{recons|ghendhe/o|lang=ine-pro}} 'to take' (compare {{etyl|cy|-}} {{term|genni|lang=cy||to delve, submerge onself}}, [[Latin]] pre''hendere'' 'to grasp, nab', pra''eda'' 'prey', {{etyl|sq|-}} {{term|zë||to catch|lang=sq}}, [[Ancient Greek]] {{term||chandánein|to hold, contain}}).

